  / Education
  %aside{style: 'background-image: url(/img/portfolio/education_header.jpg);'}
    %figcaption#education{name: 'education'}
      %h2
        Education
        %a.portfolio-header-link{href: '#education'}> #
      %div
        %p I grew up wanting to become a teacher, and when I became a programmer, I achieved my dream.
  .container
    .row
      - standard_width_div do
        %ul#education_list.list-inline.text-center
          %li
            %h3 Blogging
            %img{src: '/img/portfolio/blogging.jpg'}/
            %div
              :markdown

                I've been writing a developer-focused blog since 2011, now hosted here. At [Teehan+Lax](http://www.teehanlax.com/blog/author/ash/), I began contributing to company blog as part of my job. I still do, now on [Artsy's developer blog](http://artsy.github.io). I've also written posts for [objc.io](http://www.objc.io/contributors/).

                Blogging about has made me [a better developer and a better writer](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SjjvnrqDjpM).
          %li
            %h3 Workshops
            %img{src: '/img/portfolio/treehouse.jpg'}/
            %div
              :markdown

                In March, 2014, [Treehouse](http://teamtreehouse.com) invited me to Orlando to record a series of videos and screencasts to guide students through using Core Data to build a diary app for iOS.

                I've also given in-person workshops on subjects ranging from the basics of iOS development to functional reactive programming in Swift.
          %li
            %h3 Speaking
            %img{src: '/img/portfolio/speaking.jpg'}/
            %div
              :markdown
                I began speaking in the Toronto CocoaHeads group. Eventually, I started submitting proposals to conferences. Today, I've spoken all over the world on a variety of subjects relating to iOS development.

                Check out my [speaking page](/speaking) for more.
          %li
            %h3 Books
            %img{src: '/img/portfolio/books.png'}/
            %div
              :markdown
                Since 2012, I've written a number of books on iOS development (both with publishers and self-published). Like with blogging, writing is a very satisfying activity. I enjoy planning a route to take a reader on, considering what to teach them (and when), and turning my ideas into educational resources.

                [Check out my books page](/books) for a complete reference.

  / Photography
